9:
Wait... You're really gonna use ALL of
this?
12:
Just how many people do you think
live in Palpebra? I'm planning
something BIG.
16:
What do you use cacao for
anyways? This stuff doesn't smell
sweet.
19:
Oh, you silly head. Don't you know
about chocolate? It's the flavor of
Valentine's.
23:
I heard chocolate was made from a
bitter bean, but this is my first time
seeing it.
26:
Oh, no, no, no. These aren't cacao
BEANS. You see, my chocolate's
made from a uniiique ingredient.
37:
What you're seeing right in front of
you, ladies and gentlemen, are the
fruits of special plant-monsters!
41:
And there's nothing to freak out
about. They're real fruits! Harvested
from real plants!
47: You just said they were monsters!
52:
Yeah, but you can't tell! Or you won't
be able to after you split the fruit
open.
57:
And that's it! One peppy little shriek,
and it's over. You'd never even
suspect this thing came from a
monster. Don't let the screams
bother you either. They're not out of
pain or anythingâ€”more like a cool
sound effect.
61:
Hm. I wonder why that DOESN'T MAKE
ME FEEL BETTER.
65:
Did you forget? Lilie appointed us to
keep you from strange ingredients.
We cannot allow you to use that
fruit!
69:
Oh, I remember. Basically, if I can
convince you monster-based
foodstuff isn't weird, I'm free to use it.
78:
Listen. I know what Lilie wants. She
wants me to act like everyone else
so I can succeed... just like everyone
else.
80: But for me, that's not enough.
84:
Palpebra's THE city for adventurers,
right? Here, we're supposed to
dream big, think outside the box,
and venture out of comfort zones...
86:
I don't want to give up on something
just because it's "abnormal."
Especially not in a place like this!
87:
The first time I tried Monster Cuisine,
I discovered smells, sensations, and
flavors I'd never even imagined...
And I want to bring people on this
journey with me!
91:
Hah. You have a lot of bark, I'll give
you that.
95:
Oops. Sorry. Got kinda carried away
there, didn't I? I might know how to
simmer sauces, but I can't simmer
down my passion.
97:
Still, I AM an adult, okay? I know the
art of compromise. We can talk
things over and figure out a recipe
that works for all of us.
102:
Such a recipe would have no
monsters in it. At all.
108:
Fine... FINE! You leave me no other
choice! I'm just gonna have to
change your minds!
113:
Chef Parfait proudly presents...
Chow Down Showdown! A
Monster-Tasting Spectacular!
123: Just one bite, and you'll understand.
131:
May I have your attention please!
Our first contender today is splendid
array of chocolates, crafted from
freshly picked cacao fruit!
134:
Now, it's YOUR task to decide if these
chocolates deserve a place on the
menu!

On your mark! Get set!
141: Why have things come to this?
144: At least this stuff LOOKS normal.
148:
As long as it doesn't scream when I
start chewing...
162:
I KNOW RIGHT?! So that's how many
votes for the cacao fruit?
167:
If only it came from a normal
animal...
176:
Light, have you TASTED this
chocolate? Why would you deprive
the world of such a MASTERPIECE?
179:
That settles it! The first ingredient on
our list is the cacao fruit! Whoo-hoo!
182:
Once I've arranged deliveries for the
rest of our harvest, what say we go
on the hunt for contender number
two?
187:
Next, we need a sweetener. And the
way we're gonna get it is...
190: By attacking that hive of Beeyonets!
202:
Whaaat? Nooo... They're just
human-sized bumbly bees! Now,
come on! Let's get buzzin'!
